Poland  rejected a cargo of rapeseed
from Ukraine because of infestation with mites, a notification
to the European Unionâ€™s food-alert system showed.  A sample of Ukrainian rapeseed tested Nov. 9 in a border
control showed 10 mites for each kilogram (2.2 pounds) of the
oilseed, according to the  notice  from Poland published online
today. The consignment was rejected at the border, detained and
re-dispatched, according to the notice.  To contact the reporter on this story:
